{
  "stem": "22237.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had no bag, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he said that if I wanted to sell him something, he'll give me some money.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I sold him some items that I saw stand-- I let him look around, and asked him what he wanted.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he saw a few things, a couple of silver things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he gave me some money, and he left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, and then I-- and I remember looking around, and I saw these-- my mother was trying, before we were deported, to make some hot tea for us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there the cups were standing on the table with the-- with-- and of course, they didn't let her.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I remember seeing these cups, and I did nothing but cry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so from then on, and then I visited this-- my-- Mrs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Friedman and visited.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then I went to her, and after that I, I stayed with some of the people because I was very much too-- very afraid to be in the house.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I, I went back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I did sleep-- I did stay in the house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In the evenings I would go back to the house because everybody was involved with their own-- especially after this Polish deportation, the other Jews became very much concerned that this will happen to them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they were also afraid to take somebody in who was already deported.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I kind of fell asleep like in a coma in the house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And after that, I remember, I woke up one night and there was a lot of noise, like the breaking of glass.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I looked out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I looked through the blinds, and I saw that there were people throwing stones through the windows that we knew-- that I knew that Jewish people lived there.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
